				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The hardware triangle is NOT halted by 0 in the period register.<br /><br />It's very normal to halt it in emulation because of the reason you mentioned. It's really hard to implement a filter than can cut it out as nicely as your analog hardware does.<br /><br />You can verify this on hardware by setting the period to 0 and turning the triangle on and off. You'll hear a popping where the the triangle starts and stops.<br /><br />My choice for NSFPlay was to halt on period 0 by default, but I gave the option to turn it off (even though my oversampling process is not good enough to suppress it entirely, it still comes through as a high pitched aliased ringing).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

