			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">As I understand it, the performance of BLEP resampling algorithms like blargg's is O(n) in the number of transitions. Doing it without hacks is fine for square and DMC because they change less often. DMC is limited to how fast writes to $4011 can occur, and square is limited to two transitions per 144 cycles because it shuts off when the period value becomes less than 8. But triangle and noise can have a transition every 1 or 2 cycles. Do GBS files routinely drive the wavetable at period $7FF (inverted vs. NES) and noise at maximum rate?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

